{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01PALqbnpWgME5kH1wTzjTJM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals confirmed:\n\n- **Root cause**: `app-user` had an empty `configure` permission on the `/app` vhost, so it was authorized to `write`/`read` but not to declare (create) queues via the management API — causing the `not_authorised` error and CrashLoop.\n- **Fix**: `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \"^app-.*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — scoped `configure` to the app's queue naming convention rather than granting blanket `.*` access.\n- **Verified**: `app-producer` pod is `1/1 Running`, `/app` vhost has `app-queue` of type `classic` with messages flowing (10 and counting), and the cluster still shows all 3 nodes running healthy. No CRDs/operators used, no data touched or lost."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":731,"cache_read_input_tokens":47885,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":731},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b98e9fed-276b-4771-b6f0-40e2dafc0cfa","uuid":"2077b595-c452-415b-8156-4b72a7cda98c","request_id":"req_011CcasPAHNqnpp5hCmFUiF3"}
